<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-04-18T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-04-18T17:00:00-05:00" n="297" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6187: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China (<persName type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-18T17:00:00-05:00">April 18, 1933—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>122. Your 336, April 18, 2 p.m.</p>
                        <p>First paragraph. This method of approach is apparently much employed and
                            must be guarded against. It affords, however, useful information.</p>
                        <p>Second paragraph. Department concurs and approves.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>